It's time to tear up our bedroom. The last room in the house that hasn't been touched except for a little decorating.
The disgusting electric fireplace and the fireplace floor have to go. We need to build a wall around the fireplace, replace the cracked plaster, and smooth it out. Then build a custom closet.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch...
The dirty part of the work is done.
We found a few dead birds in the chimney, very dried up :(
All set for the plasterer next week
The small side niche turned out well
A new closet is coming in here (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought about installing this nice little vent flap, so the fireplace doesn't get wet
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and cap. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest there🪺
The plasterer is done. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlayment is in place, I made a paper towel roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Parts for the floor are finished and can be laid. We are having tea break right now
Boo. Today progress is slow, because of super complicated cuts around the door posts, so we can have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be laid). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Done, but finally! The crowning achievement was the terrible installation manual for the new bed. We will sleep well tonight!
The floor in the hallway and all the baseboards are still missing. The decorator comes in a month, so we currently have a raw plaster look.
A little DIY work in the evening to cut or chisel the lower sections around the door posts, where the floor should fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlayment is now also in the hallway.
We finished the floor in the hallway yesterday! Then we left at 5 a.m. to pick up item 1 at Heathrow, then a nap and a final push in the hallway, the baseboards are installed. The joints will be made once the glue dries.
